President Muhammadu Buhari’s nephew, Ibrahim Dauda, has passed on. Dauda’s death was disclosed in a statement on Saturday, by the Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity to the President, Garba Shehu. He said Dauda died in Daura, Katsina state, following a prolonged illness. In a touching condolence message, the President noted that his nephew’s death had robbed the family and the Daura community of one of their finest gentlemen. He prayed to God to forgive the deceased his shortcomings and reward his noble deeds with paradise. “I am deeply touched and devastated by the passing of yet another family member, a man who had demonstrated amazing kindness and honesty in all his dealings,” Buhari said. The deceased is survived by Ibrahim, a chief administrative officer in state house, Abuja, and other children 